Text: 18/5Today we met up at 2pm.
Unfortunately, the client was busy so we were unable to meet them today so they could take us through GitLab and the existing code.
I had done some work on the draft proposal prior to the meeting but not as much as I should have.
During the meeting, we began to flesh out the draft more.
19/5We met with the client today.
They took us through the GitLab and Visual Studio and a little bit of the code.
We had a major issue today with not being able to test the code locally as it needs to connect to the server but it won't let us.
I have tried to research how to fix the issue but I don't think I understand the problem fully.
I also feel everyone including myself has now been distracted by the actual code and are not doing enough work on the proposal.
Seeing as it comes before working on the actual project we need to get it out of the way so then everyone can get to doing what we want to be doing.
20/5I have written another large chunk of the proposal but it still feels like I have done the majority.
We are meeting at 12pm today.
21/5We finally finished the presentation but I am not happy with a couple of slides.
One doesn't fit the theme and looks very unprofessional.
I aired my concerns but as it is a group project we have to compromise.
The other slide just doesn't look tidy.
Maybe I need to not try to be so perfect.
We didn't manage to quite finish the proposal but it just needs a few minor touch-ups which we will have to do tomorrow.
22/5Presented our proposal and I think it went well.
After seeing the other groups it made me less worried about our own presentation.
But on the other hand, I also shouldn't let the other presentations influence my level of expectations.
Finished off the proposal early afternoon and let Indu and Kuku have a last read through.
Indu was happy but never heard from Kuku so had to submit it without his approval.
Feeling like Kuku isn't contributing his fair share towards this project so far.
Summary.
What have been the goals for the week and what did I achieve?

To complete the proposalAchievedFelt I did more than my shareTo complete the presentationAchievedHoped to complete these early so we could start looking more into the projectNot achievedTimelines set out during the process kept being pushed backGroup members kept turning up to meetings not having completed parts that we agreed to have completed prior to meeting

What (parts of the workflow/research/development) was working well and why?Communication with InduBoth of us respond to messages promptlyMeeting with InduBoth of us are on time and present for all scheduled meetingsWhat (parts of the workflow/research/development) was not working well and why?Kuku's contribution felt to be lackingCommunication with KukuVery slow to respond to messages if he even does respondMeeting with KukuKuku missed a couple of meetings or was late

What would I do differently if I would be faced with the same situation or goals? Communicate the workload betterDivvy out the workload in chunks rather than just say to work on writing out the proposal and hope for the best

What did I learn this week and/or what am I proud of or satisfied with?I am happy with my contribution to the proposal and presentationFelt it was professional, well-formatted and of a good qualityAdded to my reflective blog daily
